    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces and add<strong> </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>dried oregano</strong> all over, give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the<strong> onion </strong>and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to one side of a separate baking tray (or two!) and set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix everything together, then add your<strong> chicken </strong>and turn several times until fully coated in all the spices \u2013 this is your<strong> paprika chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>paprika chicken </strong>to the tray[s] with the onion and tomato and drizzle everything with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the vegetables have softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the bowl and stir it all together \u2013 this is your<strong> aioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min, turning occasionally, until starting to char and soften \u2013 this is your <strong>charred pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>cooked paprika chicken</strong> finely on a clean board</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanish-style-chicken-and-charred-pepper-salad-with-aioli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place the<strong> salad </strong>on a plate and top with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong>, <strong>roasted onion </strong>and<strong> tomato</strong>,<strong> sliced paprika chicken </strong>and <strong>charred pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> Spanish-style chicken & charred pepper salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle the<strong> aioli </strong>all over and top with your <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
